{"lemma":"فَضْلُ","slug":"فَضْلُ","root":"ف.ض.ل","root_slug":"ف-ض-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ض-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"فَضْل","root":"فضل","pos":"N","occurrence_count":84},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":11},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n34074","n34080","n34081"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%8E%D8%B6%D9%92%D9%84%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to remain, to be left over","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to exceed or outdo (especially in virtue, merit, or worth); to outworth","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to become meritorious; to become illustrious"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to deem more favorable, to prefer, to favor","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make dominant, to privilege","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make dominant, to privilege; to make distinct or prominent, to distinguish, to honor, to grace","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"grace, favor (especially when seen as unmerited or unconditional); courtesy","tags":["uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"grace, favor (especially when seen as unmerited or unconditional); courtesy; a blessing, an honor, a generous gift, a bestowment","tags":["countable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"distinction","tags":["uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"distinction; merit","tags":["uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"leftovers, remnants","tags":["uncountable"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n34074","headword_ar":"فَضَلَ","root":"fDl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDila","text_ar":"فَضِلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDila","text_ar":"فَضِلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; three syn. dial. vars.; (S, O, Msb, K;) the second mentioned by ISk; and the third [said to be] anomalous and unparalleled; (S, O;) [but] it is a compound of two thereof, (S, O, Msb, K,) accord. to the companions of Sb, (S, O,) i. e. a compound of the second and the third, (K,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naEima","text_ar":"نَعِمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"having for its aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yanoEumu","text_ar":"يَنْعُمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Sb, S, O, Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nakila","text_ar":"نَكِلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yanokulu","text_ar":"يَنْكُلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [but this I do not find in its proper art.,] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaDira","text_ar":"حَضِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaHoDuru","text_ar":"يَحْضُرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [but this is disallowed by some,] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fariga","text_ar":"فَرِغَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaforugu","text_ar":"يَفْرُغُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", among perfect verbs, (Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mit~a","text_ar":"مِتَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamuwtu","text_ar":"تَمُوتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dimota","text_ar":"دِمْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taduwmu","text_ar":"تَدُومُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Sb, S, O, Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kidota","text_ar":"كِدْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"takuwdu","text_ar":"تَكُودُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Sb, S;) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDolN","text_ar":"فَضْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, * O, * Msb, K: *) all signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It exceeded;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, redundant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"superfluous;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaAda","text_ar":"زَادَ"},{"kind":"text","text":";] being used in relation to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfaDolu","text_ar":"الفَضْلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, MF, TA) meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alz~iyaAdapu","text_ar":"الزِّيَادَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as Ibn-Es-Seed says, (MF, TA,) [i. e.] as meaning the contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aqoSu","text_ar":"النَّقْصُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, TA:) or the first of the three, i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fDala","text_ar":"فضَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDolN","text_ar":"فَضْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", signifies thus,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaAda","text_ar":"زَادَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuDolN","text_ar":"فُضْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuDulN","text_ar":"فُضُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are also inf. ns. [of the same, i. e.] signifying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ziyaAdapN","text_ar":"زِيَادَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in the saying, in a trad., accord. to different relaters,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a lil~`hi malaAy^ikapF say~aArapF fuDolFA EalaY AlmalaAy^ikapi","text_ar":"اـِنَّ لِلّٰهِ مَلَايِكَةً سَيَّارَةً فُضْلًا عَلَى المَلَايِكَةِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almurat~abiyna maEa AlxalaAy^iqi","text_ar":"المُرَتَّبِينَ مَعَ الخَلَايِقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuDulFA","text_ar":"فُضُلًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily to God belong angels who occupy themselves in ranging about, in addition to the angels who are stationed among the created,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"human and other, beings"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) and all the three dial. vars. mentioned above signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it remained"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of a greater quantity or number]; syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqiYa","text_ar":"بَقِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, * O, * Msb;) you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDala minohu $aYo'N","text_ar":"فَضَلَ مِنْهُ شَىْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDila","text_ar":"فَضِلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDila","text_ar":"فَضِلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"somewhat remained thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O:) or from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfaDolu","text_ar":"الفَضْلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albaqiy~apu","text_ar":"البَقِيَّةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDala","text_ar":"فَضَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSara","text_ar":"نَصَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [i. e. aor."},{"kind":"text","text":",] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDila","text_ar":"فَضِلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hasiba","text_ar":"حَسِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [implying that the aor. is"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":",] (K,) [accord. to the TK meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it had somewhat remaining,"},{"kind":"text","text":"but accord. to SM,] using these verbs [which are said by him to be like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSara","text_ar":"نَصَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samiEa","text_ar":"سَمِعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hasiba","text_ar":"حَسِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the last as mentioned by Lh,] in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDala minohu","text_ar":"فَضَلَ مِنْهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aYo'N","text_ar":"شَىْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[expl. above]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDala","text_ar":"فَضَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is trans. as well as intrans.] One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDalahu","text_ar":"فَضَلَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDala Ealayohi","text_ar":"فَضَلَ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [aor."},{"kind":"text","text":",] inf. ns."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDolN","text_ar":"فَضْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuDuwlN","text_ar":"فُضُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [but see a distinction made between these two words voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDolN","text_ar":"فَضْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below,] meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, exceeded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excelled, him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA.) See also 4. [And see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDolN","text_ar":"فَضْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"below, last signification.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfaDolu","text_ar":"الفَضْلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The overcoming,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"surpassing, in highness, elevation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eminence, of rank, condition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"estimation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"has but one form of verb,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDala","text_ar":"فَضَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaEada","text_ar":"قَعَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaqoEudu","text_ar":"يَقْعُدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": he who relates the saying of the poet,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"wajadonaA naho$alFA faDalato fuqayomaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We found,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"have found, that Nahshal"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the tribe so called)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"overcame"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"have overcome"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fukeym"},{"kind":"text","text":"(another tribe)], pronouncing the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"D","text_ar":"ض"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fDlt","text_ar":"فضلت"},{"kind":"text","text":"] with kesr, errs; not distinguishing between the two meanings: so says Ibn-Es-Seed, in the book entitled “ Kitáb el-Fark: ” and Es- Seymuree says, in his book entitled “ Kitáb etTebsireh, ”"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDala","text_ar":"فَضَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSara","text_ar":"نَصَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yanoSuru","text_ar":"يَنْصُرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfaDolu","text_ar":"الفَضْلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the ruling"},{"kind":"text","text":"[others]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as a chief, lord,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"master."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDalahu","text_ar":"فَضَلَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also [simply]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He overcame him; surpassed him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gained ascendency,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the mastery, over him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) See also 3."}],"source_refs":["S","O","Msb","K","Sb","MF","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n34080","headword_ar":"فَضْلٌ","root":"fDl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[an inf. n.: (see 1, throughout:) and also a simple subst., signifying]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An exceeding, a redundant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a superfluous, quantum"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of anything, good or evil];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an excess, a redundance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a superfluity;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ziyaAdapN","text_ar":"زِيَادَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Mgh, Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naqoSN","text_ar":"نَقْصٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O, K:) [and often meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"superabundance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exuberance;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"surpassingness, superiority,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excellence."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY gayorihi","text_ar":"عَلَى غَيْرِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"over another,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"others, than him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"preponderance:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuDuwlN","text_ar":"فُضُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb, K:) and this is sometimes used as a sing.; (Er-Rághib, Msb;) and [thus used] relates to a thing [or quality] in which is no good; (Er-Rághib, Mgh, Msb;) by a predominant application; whence the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuDuwlN bilaA faDolK","text_ar":"فُضُولٌ بِلَا فَضْلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excess without excellence"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (Mgh;) and hence the rel. n. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuDuwliY~N","text_ar":"فُضُولِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is formed from it: (Er-Rághib, Msb, TA;) [see this last word, one of the explanations of which shows that a particular meaning of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuDuwlN","text_ar":"فُضُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quality of busying oneself with that which does not concern him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] accord. to Er-Rághib,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDolN","text_ar":"فَضْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an excess"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in respect of a property or quality, or of an acquisition,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"above moderateness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and this is of two sorts; such as is commended, as the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fDl","text_ar":"فضل"},{"kind":"text","text":"of knowledge, or science ; and such as is discommended, as the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fSl","text_ar":"فصل"},{"kind":"text","text":"of anger at that whereat it is not necessary: but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDalN","text_ar":"فَضَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is more used in relation to that which is commended; and [the pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuDuwlN","text_ar":"فُضُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in relation to that which is discommended. when the former is used of an excess [in respect of some attribute, of our of two things above the other, it is of three sorts;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fDl","text_ar":"فضل"},{"kind":"text","text":"of kind, as of the animal kind above the vegetable kind; and of species, as of man above other animals; and of the individual, as of one man above another; the first and second of which three are essential attributes, such that he who is deficient in [either of] them cannot do away with his deficiency and acquire"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fDl","text_ar":"فضل"},{"kind":"text","text":", as,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for instance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"the horse, and the ass, which cannot acquire the excellence ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDiylap","text_ar":"فَضِيلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":") of the human being; but the third may be accidental, such that the way may be found to acquire it, and of this sort are ability, wealth, rank or station, and power: and it signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any gift whereof the giving to the recipient thereof is not obligatory:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a free gift,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or gratuity; and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an act of bounty"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grace; a favour; a benefit;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bounty"},{"kind":"text","text":"as an abstract term;] as in the saying [in the Kur iv. 36],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@soA^aluwA","text_ar":"وَا@سْاَلُوا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@ll~`ha mino faDolihi","text_ar":"ا@للّٰهَ مِنْ فَضْلِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And ask ye God of his free gift,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of his bounty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or (as expl. in the Ksh and by Bd)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of his exhaustless treasures"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and in the saying in the Kur [v. 59 and lvii. 21 and lxii. 4],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*`lika faDolu","text_ar":"ذٰلِكَ فَضْلُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@ll~`hi yuw^otiyhi mano ya$aA='u","text_ar":"ا@للّٰهِ يُوْتِيهِ مَنْ يَشَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That is the free gift of God; He giveth it to whom He willeth"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; which comprises the three sorts of excellences ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDaAy^il","text_ar":"فَضَايِل"},{"kind":"text","text":") [mentioned above]: thus says Er-Rághib: El-Muná- wee says, [explaining one of its meanings,] in the “ Towkeef, ” that it is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"commencing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"originating, of an act of beneficence without an efficient cause"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e., app.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not by reason of any obligation"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A portion remaining,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,) of a thing, such as food &c., and of water in the leathern water-bag, and of wine or beverage in the vessel; (TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDolapN","text_ar":"فَضْلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuDaAlapN","text_ar":"فُضَالَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify the same, (K, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a redundant portion"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S and O and Msb in explanation of these two words) of a thing: (S, O:) whence the saying of the vulgar, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lilofaDiyli","text_ar":"لِلْفَضِيلِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfaDolapu","text_ar":"الفَضْلَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The remaining portion"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the wine or beverage ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is for the excel-lent"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA yumonaEu faDolu","text_ar":"لَا يُمْنَعُ فَضْلُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaA='i liyumonaEa bihi AlkalaA^u","text_ar":"المَا=ءِ لِيُمْنَعَ بِهِ الكَلَاُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The redundance of water shall not be denied that the herbage be thereby denied"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA, in the present art.:) meaning that when there is a well in the desert, with herbage near it, and a person prevents others from drawing water, he thereby prevents the latter from availing themselves of the herbage; for when a man comes with his camels, and pastures them upon that herbage, and does not then water them, thirst kills them. (TA in art"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"klA^","text_ar":"كلا"},{"kind":"text","text":",) And it is said in another trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDolu AlA_izaAri fiY Aln~aAri","text_ar":"فَضْلُ الاـِزَارِ فِى النَّارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The redundant portion of the waist-wrapper is in the fire"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Hell]; meaning what one drags [thereof] upon the around, by reason of pride. (TA;) And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY yadihi faDolu Alz~imaAmi","text_ar":"فِى يَدِهِ فَضْلُ الزِّمَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In his hand is"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the end of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zmAm","text_ar":"زمام"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nose-rein"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the camel]. (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aAtu AlfuDuwli","text_ar":"ذَاتُ الفُضُولِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfDuwli","text_ar":"الفضُولِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with damm and with fet-h, ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The thing having redundant portions"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is the name of the coat of mail of the Prophet, which was thus called because having redundance and ampleness. (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuDuwlu","text_ar":"فُضُولُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlganaAy^imi","text_ar":"الغَنَايِمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The remains of the spoils when they are divided"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) such as a single horse, or a single camel (KL.) And by the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuDuwl","text_ar":"فُضُول"},{"kind":"text","text":"of women are meant The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remains of the menstrual discharge"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 107: see, there, explanations of a verse in which this occurs.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hilofu AlfuDuwli","text_ar":"حِلْفُ الفُضُولِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The confederacy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"covenant, of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fDwl","text_ar":"فضول"},{"kind":"text","text":", a word which is here of uncertain meaning,] is thus explained: Háshim and Zuhrah and Teym [accord. to the CK Teymà] went in to 'Abd-Allah Ibn-Jud'án, and united in a confederacy to repel wrongdoing, and to exact the due from the wrongdoer; and it was thus called because they bound themselves by their confederacy not to leave in the possession of any one aught remaining [of property] whereof he aught despond any one, without their taking it for him [i. e. the latter] from him [i. e. the former] (O, K, TA: [in the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaZolimuhu A^aHadN","text_ar":"يَظْلِمُهُ اَحَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a mistake for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yZlmh","text_ar":"يظلمه"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHadFA","text_ar":"اَحَدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) or it was thus called as being likened to a confederacy, or covenant, which was made of old, at Mekkeh, in the days of Jurhum, to act with mutual equity, and to take for the weak from the strong, and for the stranger from the resident, and in which three men, every one of whom was named El-Fadl, joined: and it was also called that of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maTay~abuwn","text_ar":"مَطَيَّبُون"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA. [See art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tyb","text_ar":"طيب"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b3-  The saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA yamoliku dirohamFA faDolFA Eano diynaArK","text_ar":"لَا يَمْلِكُ دِرْهَمًا فَضْلًا عَنْ دِينَارٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the like may be said of other sayings similar to it, means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He does not possess a dirhem nor a deenár"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or rather"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"much less a deenár"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: it is as though one said,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he does not possess a dirhem: how then should he possess a deenár?"},{"kind":"text","text":"for the negation of that which is much is a necessary consequence of the negation of that which is little:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDolFA","text_ar":"فَضْلًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is here in the accus case as an inf. n.; the implied meaning being"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faqada miloka dirohamK faqodFA","text_ar":"فَقَدَ مِلْكَ دِرْهَمٍ فَقْدًا"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2413},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yafoDulu Eano faqodi miloki dynaArK","text_ar":"يَفْضُلُ عَنْ فَقْدِ مِلْكِ دينَارٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or rather"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yafoqidu","text_ar":"يَفْقِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he lacks the possession of a dirhem with a lacking exceeding the lacking of the possession of a deenár"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb:) Kutb-ed-Deen Esh-Sheerázee says, (Msb, TA,) in the Expos. of the “ Miftáh, ” (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDolFA","text_ar":"فَضْلًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used in a case in which the inferior [of two things] is deemed a thing of which the existence is improbable, and the impossibility of the existence of a thing that is above it is meant thereby; wherefore it occurs between two phrases differing in meaning; and it is mostly used after a particle of negation: (Msb, TA:) AHei says that he had not found any authority for it in the [classical] language of the Arabs. (Msb. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baloha","text_ar":"بَلْهَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is used in a somewhat similar manner.])"}],"source_refs":["S","O","K","Mgh","Msb","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n34081","headword_ar":"فُضُلٌ","root":"fDl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wearing a single garment, such as is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mifoDalN","text_ar":"مِفْضَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; an epithet applied to a woman; (S, Mgh, * O, K;) and also to a man; (S, O, K;) like ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutafaD~ilN","text_ar":"مُتَفَضِّلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (O, K:) it is of the dial. of Nejd; like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furujN","text_ar":"فُرُجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the dial. of El-Yemen. (L in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"frj","text_ar":"فرج"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b2-  And A woman"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proud,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"self-conceited,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so in her gait; who makes a portion of her skirt to be redundant"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that it drags upon the ground when she walks"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mifoDalN","text_ar":"مِفْضَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places."}],"source_refs":["O","K"]}]}}